<p>for the 3rd Artillery Brigade had got lost or rather sank in a lighter coming ashore. I'm hoping that its not true as I will miss my letters very much. The young Donkey which I mentioned was born some weeks back is growing fast and frolicking around our lines quite at home with its old Mother. A male donkey has joined the mother a few weeks back &amp; our lads make use of it for transport purposes.</p>
<p>Tuesday 24th August<br/>Still gusty and blowy. I received some papers but no letters &amp; was a bit disappointed. Am still acting as Quartermaster Sergeant &amp; Pay my daily visit to the beach for victuals etc.</p>
<p>Wednesday 25th Aug<br/>The other day I met Wilson brother of Jack Wilson who is with our 5th Light Horse. He is acting in Col</p>
